# CMC-Learning — Agile User Stories (Jira-Ready)

**Project**: CMC-Learning E-Learning Platform
**Team**: 4 Developers (Dev A, Dev B, Dev C, Dev D)
**Methodology**: Scrum — 2-week sprints
**Total Estimated Story Points**: ~170

---

## Developer Assignment Strategy

| Developer | Focus Areas |
|-----------|-------------|
| **Dev A** | Authentication, Profile, Security |
| **Dev B** | Courses Management, Ratings |
| **Dev C** | Resources, Search & Filtering |
| **Dev D** | Forum / Q&A, Admin Dashboard |

---

## Epic Overview

| Epic ID | Epic Name | Priority | Total SP |
|---------|-----------|----------|----------|
| EP-01 | Authentication & Authorization | High | 26 |
| EP-02 | Course Management | High | 29 |
| EP-03 | Resource Management | High | 21 |
| EP-04 | Ratings System | Medium | 13 |
| EP-05 | Forum / Q&A | Medium | 26 |
| EP-06 | Search & Filtering | Medium | 13 |
| EP-07 | Admin Dashboard | High | 26 |
| EP-08 | Profile Management | Medium | 10 |
| EP-09 | Platform Shell & Navigation | High | 8 |

---

## EP-01 — Authentication & Authorization

> **Goal**: Allow users to register, log in, and access features based on their role.
> **Assigned to**: Dev A

---

### US-01.1 — User Registration

**As a** visitor,
**I want** to register with my email, name, password, and role,
**So that** I can access the platform.

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Priority | High |
| Story Points | 5 |
| Sprint | Sprint 1 |

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] User can select role: Stagiaire or Formateur
- [ ] Stagiaire can select speciality + year
- [ ] Email must be unique — display error if taken
- [ ] Password requires minimum 6 characters
- [ ] Password confirmation field must match
- [ ] On success, user is redirected to Dashboard
- [ ] JWT token is stored in localStorage

**Sub-Tasks:**
| Task | Assignee | Est. |
|------|----------|------|
| Create RegisterPage UI with form fields | Dev A | 2h |
| Implement form validation (client-side) | Dev A | 1h |
| Connect to POST `/api/auth/register` | Dev A | 1h |
| Create `registerUser` async thunk in authSlice | Dev A | 1h |
| Handle error states and display messages | Dev A | 1h |

---

### US-01.2 — User Login

**As a** registered user,
**I want** to log in with my email and password,
**So that** I can access my account.

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Priority | High |
| Story Points | 5 |
| Sprint | Sprint 1 |

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] User enters email + password
- [ ] On success, JWT is stored and user is redirected to Dashboard
- [ ] On failure, a clear error message is displayed
- [ ] Loading spinner is shown during request

**Sub-Tasks:**
| Task | Assignee | Est. |
|------|----------|------|
| Create LoginPage UI | Dev A | 1.5h |
| Create `loginUser` async thunk | Dev A | 1h |
| Store JWT + user in localStorage and Redux | Dev A | 1h |
| Handle API errors and display feedback | Dev A | 1h |
| Add redirect to Dashboard on success | Dev A | 0.5h |

---

### US-01.3 — JWT Token Management

**As a** logged-in user,
**I want** my session to persist across page refreshes,
**So that** I don't have to log in every time.

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Priority | High |
| Story Points | 3 |
| Sprint | Sprint 1 |

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] JWT token is auto-attached to every API request via Axios interceptor
- [ ] On 401 response, user is redirected to login and token cleared
- [ ] On app load, user state is restored from localStorage

**Sub-Tasks:**
| Task | Assignee | Est. |
|------|----------|------|
| Configure Axios interceptor for Authorization header | Dev A | 1h |
| Implement 401 response interceptor with redirect | Dev A | 1h |
| Restore auth state from localStorage on app init | Dev A | 1h |

---

### US-01.4 — Protected Routes

**As a** platform admin,
**I want** unauthenticated users blocked from protected pages,
**So that** only logged-in users can access the platform.

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Priority | High |
| Story Points | 5 |
| Sprint | Sprint 1 |

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] ProtectedRoute redirects unauthenticated users to `/login`
- [ ] RoleGuard blocks users without the required role → `/unauthorized`
- [ ] Admin routes only accessible by admin role
- [ ] Formateur routes accessible by formateur + admin
- [ ] Unauthorized page displays clear message with back link

**Sub-Tasks:**
| Task | Assignee | Est. |
|------|----------|------|
| Create [ProtectedRoute](file:///c:/cmclearning/src/routes/ProtectedRoute.tsx#4-21) component | Dev A | 1h |
| Create [RoleGuard](file:///c:/cmclearning/src/routes/RoleGuard.tsx#9-22) component | Dev A | 1h |
| Create [UnauthorizedPage](file:///c:/cmclearning/src/app/UnauthorizedPage.tsx#5-21) | Dev A | 0.5h |
| Configure route nesting in [router.tsx](file:///c:/cmclearning/src/routes/router.tsx) | Dev A | 1.5h |
| Test all role-based access scenarios | Dev A | 1h |

---

### US-01.5 — Logout

**As a** logged-in user,
**I want** to log out of my account,
**So that** I can secure my session.

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Priority | High |
| Story Points | 2 |
| Sprint | Sprint 1 |

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Logout button in Navbar
- [ ] On click, JWT and user data cleared from localStorage + Redux
- [ ] User redirected to login page

**Sub-Tasks:**
| Task | Assignee | Est. |
|------|----------|------|
| Add logout action to authSlice | Dev A | 0.5h |
| Add logout button to Navbar | Dev A | 0.5h |
| Clear storage and redirect on logout | Dev A | 0.5h |

---

### US-01.6 — Auto-Redirect Authenticated Users

**As a** logged-in user,
**I want** to be redirected to Dashboard if I visit `/login`,
**So that** I don't see the login page unnecessarily.

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Priority | Low |
| Story Points | 2 |
| Sprint | Sprint 2 |

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] If user is authenticated and visits `/login` or `/register`, redirect to `/dashboard`

**Sub-Tasks:**
| Task | Assignee | Est. |
|------|----------|------|
| Add redirect logic in LoginPage and RegisterPage | Dev A | 1h |

---

### US-01.7 — Password Reset (Future)

**As a** user who forgot my password,
**I want** to reset it via email,
**So that** I can regain access.

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Priority | Low |
| Story Points | 5 |
| Sprint | Backlog |

