## EP-02 — Course Management

> **Goal**: Allow formateurs to create/manage courses and stagiaires to browse/view them.
> **Assigned to**: Dev B

---

### US-02.1 — View Courses List

**As a** stagiaire,
**I want** to see a list of all available courses,
**So that** I can find courses relevant to me.

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Priority | High |
| Story Points | 5 |
| Sprint | Sprint 1 |

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Courses displayed in responsive grid (1/2/3 columns)
- [ ] Each card shows: thumbnail, title, description, formateur, rating, speciality
- [ ] Loading spinner while fetching
- [ ] Empty state when no courses found
- [ ] Pagination if > 12 courses

**Sub-Tasks:**
| Task | Assignee | Est. |
|------|----------|------|
| Create [CourseCard](file:///c:/cmclearning/src/features/courses/components/CourseCard.tsx#11-56) component | Dev B | 1.5h |
| Create [CoursesPage](file:///c:/cmclearning/src/features/courses/pages/CoursesPage.tsx#11-133) with grid layout | Dev B | 2h |
| Create `coursesSlice` with `fetchCourses` thunk | Dev B | 1.5h |
| Create `coursesService.getAll()` | Dev B | 0.5h |
| Add pagination component | Dev B | 1h |

---

### US-02.2 — Course Details Page

**As a** stagiaire,
**I want** to see full details of a course,
**So that** I can understand its content before studying.

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Priority | High |
| Story Points | 5 |
| Sprint | Sprint 1 |

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Hero banner with thumbnail/gradient fallback
- [ ] Displays: title, description, content, speciality, year, formateur, date, rating
- [ ] Lists attached resources with download buttons
- [ ] Shows edit/delete buttons for owner (formateur) and admin only
- [ ] Back button to courses list

**Sub-Tasks:**
| Task | Assignee | Est. |
|------|----------|------|
| Create [CourseDetailsPage](file:///c:/cmclearning/src/features/courses/pages/CourseDetailsPage.tsx#18-146) UI | Dev B | 2h |
| Create `fetchCourseById` thunk | Dev B | 1h |
| Display resources section | Dev B | 1h |
| Conditional edit/delete buttons per role | Dev B | 1h |

---

### US-02.3 — Create Course (Formateur)

**As a** formateur,
**I want** to create a new course with title, description, content, speciality, and year,
**So that** my students can access my teaching material.

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Priority | High |
| Story Points | 5 |
| Sprint | Sprint 2 |

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Only formateurs and admins can access the create form
- [ ] Form fields: title, description, content (textarea), speciality (dropdown), year, thumbnail (optional)
- [ ] Validation: title and description required
- [ ] On success, redirect to new course details
- [ ] Success toast notification

**Sub-Tasks:**
| Task | Assignee | Est. |
|------|----------|------|
| Create `CreateCoursePage` with form | Dev B | 2h |
| Implement `coursesService.create()` with FormData | Dev B | 1h |
| Add route guard for formateur role | Dev B | 0.5h |
| Add success redirect and toast | Dev B | 0.5h |

